      "span_id": "p207_s0001",
      "text": "INCITS xxx-200x Link Services Rev 1.61 November 3, 2006",
      "bbox": [
        301.08,
        37.27,
        539.95,
        47.32
      ],
      "block_index": 1,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p207_s0002",
      "text": " 188",
      "bbox": [
        518.28,
        723.59,
        537.71,
        734.7
      ],
      "block_index": 2,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p207_s0003",
      "text": "An EVFP transaction occurs between an EVFP Initiator and an EVFP Responder. An EVFP transac-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        57.65,
        540.07,
        68.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p207_s0004",
      "text": "tion (see figure 7) is identified by a unique Transaction Identifier (T_ID), and consists of a synchroniz-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        69.65,
        539.92,
        80.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p207_s0005",
      "text": "ing phase (EVFP_SYNC) followed by a commit phase (EVFP_COMMIT).",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        81.65,
        418.68,
        92.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p207_s0006",
      "text": "The VF_ID value FEFh is used by the EVFP protocol for certain operations and is referred to as Con-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        502.97,
        540.01,
        514.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p207_s0007",
      "text": "trol VF_ID. The EVFP protocol, during the N_Port Initialization, proceeds as follows:",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        514.96,
        465.96,
        526.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p207_s0008",
      "text": "1) The EVFP Initiator shall start the EVFP transaction by sending the EVFP_SYNC message (see",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        538.96,
        540.05,
        550.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p207_s0009",
      "text": "4.2.43.2) to the EVFP Responder. In the EVFP_SYNC message, the EVFP Initiator shall spec-",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        550.96,
        539.95,
        562.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p207_s0010",
      "text": "ify the Transaction Identifier, and shall send its Core N_Port_Name if N_Port or its Core",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        562.96,
        540.0,
        574.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p207_s0011",
      "text": "Switch_Name if F_Port, together with its Tagging Administrative Status (see 4.2.43.2.2), Port",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        574.96,
        539.79,
        586.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p207_s0012",
      "text": "VF_ID (see 4.2.43.2.3) and Locally-Enabled VF_ID List (see 4.2.43.2.4). On sending the",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        586.96,
        538.83,
        598.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p207_s0013",
      "text": "EVFP_SYNC message the EVFP Initiator enables the reception of VFT tagged frames;",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        598.96,
        506.77,
        610.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 6,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p207_s0014",
      "text": "2) The EVFP Responder shall reply with an LS_ACC carrying its Core Switch_Name if F_Port or",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        622.96,
        540.0,
        634.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p207_s0015",
      "text": "its Core N_Port_Name if N_Port, together with its Tagging Administrative Status, Port VF_ID",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        635.02,
        539.97,
        646.14
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p207_s0016",
      "text": "and Locally-Enabled VF_ID List. Then the EVFP Responder shall determine if VFT Tagging",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        647.02,
        540.01,
        658.14
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p207_s0017",
      "text": "has to be enabled on the link, according to table 126. If VFT Tagging has to be enabled, the",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        659.02,
        539.84,
        670.14
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p207_s0018",
      "text": "EVFP Responder shall go to step 3. If VFT Tagging has not to be enabled, the EVFP Respond-",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        671.02,
        540.08,
        682.14
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p207_s0019",
      "text": "er shall check the received peer’s Port VF_ID:",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        683.02,
        325.58,
        694.14
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 6,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
